+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XqvX7c1P1q5Jh6LXHBRqUs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the codebase:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration\n\nI've thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here's a complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/package.json` - Project metadata and dependencies\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Test runner configuration\n- `/workspace/src/` - Source code\n  - `db.ts` - Database setup and seeding\n  - `models.ts` - TypeScript interfaces\n  - `errors.ts` - Error handling classes\n  - `server.ts` - Express app initialization\n  - `routes.ts` - API route handlers\n  - `seed.ts` - Database seeding script\n- `/workspace/tests/` - Test files\n  - `notes.test.ts` - CRUD operations tests\n  - `search.test.ts` - Search functionality tests\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKAGE.JSON DEPENDENCIES\n\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",    // SQLite3 database\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"            // Web framework\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",             // Test framework\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/*\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",          // HTTP testing\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"                 // TypeScript execution\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - Compile TypeScript to JavaScript\n- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint\n- `npm run test` - Run Vitest test suite\n- `npm run seed` - Seed database with initial data\n\n---\n\n## 3. DATABASE SCHEMA (src/db.ts)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/db.ts`\n\n**Notes Table:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL,\n  body TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',                        -- JSON array as string\n  created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n)\n```\n\n**Pragmas:**\n- `journal_mode = WAL` - Write-Ahead Logging for better concurrency\n- `foreign_keys = ON` - Enable foreign key constraints\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `createDatabase(path?: string): Database.Database` - Creates SQLite database (in-memory if no path)\n- `seedDatabase(db: Database.Database): void` - Populates database with 50 sample notes across categories (programming, cooking, travel, health, science, etc.)\n- `getSeedNotes()` - Returns array of 50 hardcoded sample notes\n\n---\n\n## 4. DATA MODELS (src/models.ts)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/models.ts`\n\n```typescript\ninterface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string;              // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];          // Optional array of tag strings\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;          // Search result snippet (with <mark> tags)\n  rank: number;             // Relevance ranking\n}\n\ninterface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. ERROR HANDLING (src/errors.ts)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/errors.ts`\n\n**Custom Error Classes:**\n- `NotFoundError` (HTTP 404) - Resource not found\n- `ValidationError` (HTTP 400) - Validation failures\n\n**Error Handler Middleware:**\n```typescript\nerrorHandler(err, req, res, next)\n```\n- Catches and formats errors\n- Returns appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON error messages\n- Logs unhandled errors to console\n\n---\n\n## 6. SERVER SETUP (src/server.ts)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/server.ts`\n\n**Functions:**\n- `createApp(dbPath?: string): App` - Creates Express app with database and routes\n- `createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App` - Creates app and seeds database with initial data\n\n**App Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n```\n\n**Middleware:**\n- `express.json()` - JSON body parser\n- Routes from `createRoutes(db)`\n- Error handler middleware\n\n**Server Startup:**\n- Runs on port from `process.env.PORT` or defaults to 3000\n- Auto-starts when run directly\n\n---\n\n## 7. API ROUTES (src/routes.ts)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/src/routes.ts`\n\n### Core CRUD Endpoints:\n\n**GET /notes**\n- Returns all notes (most recent first)\n- Optional query parameter: `?tag=X` - filters notes by tag\n\n**GET /notes/:id**\n- Returns single note by ID\n- Returns 404 if not found\n\n**POST /notes**\n- Creates new note\n- Required: title, body\n- Optional: tags (array)\n- Returns 201 with created note\n- Validates: title and body must not be empty\n\n**PUT /notes/:id**\n- Updates existing note (partial updates supported)\n- Returns 404 if not found\n- Auto-updates `updated_at` timestamp\n\n**DELETE /notes/:id**\n- Deletes note\n- Returns 204 (No Content)\n- Returns 404 if not found\n\n### Implementation Details:\n- All routes wrapped in try-catch for error handling\n- Uses prepared statements for SQL injection prevention\n- Tag filtering uses `json_each()` SQLite function\n\n---\n\n## 8. TEST FILES\n\n### A. notes.test.ts (CRUD Tests)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/notes.test.ts`\n\n**15 Test Cases:**\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\n**Test Setup:**\n- Uses Vitest with Supertest for HTTP testing\n- Creates fresh in-memory database for each test\n- Cleans up database connection after each test\n\n### B. search.test.ts (Search/Suggest Tests)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/search.test.ts`\n\n**20 Test Cases:**\n\n**Search Functionality (Tests 1-10):**\n1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n2. GET /notes/search?q=keyword results have snippet field\n3. Snippets contain <mark> tags around matched terms\n4. Results are ranked by relevance (most relevant first)\n5. GET /notes/search?q=\"exact phrase\" matches exact phrases\n6. Search returns id, title, snippet, rank fields\n7. GET /notes/search?q=nonexistent returns empty array\n8. GET /notes/search without q returns 400\n9. GET /notes/search?q= (empty) returns 400\n\n**Pagination (Tests 10-12):**\n10. Pagination: page=1 returns first 20 results\n11. Pagination: page=2 returns next results\n12. Pagination response includes total count\n\n**Suggest Functionality (Tests 13-15):**\n13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. GET /notes/search/suggest?q= returns 400\n\n**FTS Sync Tests (Tests 16-18):**\n16. FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search\n17. FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search\n18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n\n**Robustness Tests (Tests 19-20):**\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n**Expected Endpoints (from tests):**\n- GET /notes/search?q=query\n- GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix\n- Both return JSON with structured results\n\n---\n\n## 9. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n**tsconfig.json:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Strict type checking enabled\n- Source maps and declaration files generated\n- Output directory: ./dist\n\n**vitest.config.ts:**\n- Global test APIs enabled\n- Test timeout: 10 seconds\n\n---\n\n## 10. SEED DATA\n\n50 sample